> I find the biggest advantage of objects over records to be the same as =

> polymorphic variants over classic variants:
No surprise, the duality between sum types (normal variant) and record=20
types (duality mean that they can encode
one another through a functional encoding) can be lifted to objects for=20
records ans polymorphic variants for sum ...

In Ocaml, the polymorphic variant sare a bit too limited to have the=20
full duality. To do it one would need the
type system to know that in (match t with `A -> ... | x -> ...) x can=20
not use `A. Nervertheless, J. Garrigue modular evaluator
is a bery nice illustration of this (look at his web page for the paper).=


The problem is to have tuples, records, objects and modules to be only=20
one thing (and by the way require that variant always have exactly one=20
argument),
so that you do not have to choose which approach you prefer ...


Cheers,

